WEBVTT

00:08.259 --> 00:11.843
Do you have a good shot of me?
I want the kids to see.

00:11.929 --> 00:14.671
Well, it’s a little jiggly.

00:14.765 --> 00:17.051
- Then again, so is—
— Don’t you dare, Marty!

00:17.143 --> 00:21.807
Oh. If we cut across the field,
we can beat the others
to the river!

00:21.898 --> 00:24.184
It’s a tour, Ruth.
It’s not a competition.

00:24.275 --> 00:26.561
Whoo—hoo!
This is fun!

00:28.070 --> 00:30.106
Come on, you slowpoke!

00:31.949 --> 00:33.564
[ Shrieks ]

00:34.619 --> 00:36.280
Oh, Ruthy!

00:38.164 --> 00:41.748
- Ruthy! Ruthy! Ruthy!
— I can’t feel my face!

00:41.834 --> 00:43.790
No, it’s tingling.

00:43.878 --> 00:45.664
Bugs! Ruthy,
you’re covered in bugs!

00:45.755 --> 00:47.416
Oh! Oh! Get ’em off me!

00:47.506 --> 00:49.588
Oh! Marty, I’m getting bit!

00:49.675 --> 00:51.540
Just calm down, Ruthy!
Just calm down!

00:51.636 --> 00:53.752
Oh, my God! What? What?

00:53.846 --> 00:56.258
Oh!
[Groaning]

00:56.349 --> 00:58.214
[Yelping, Whimpering]

00:58.309 --> 01:00.516
The kids are not
gonna believe this.

01:00.603 --> 01:03.515
— Get them off of me!
- Look at that!
[ Chuckles ]

01:08.110 --> 01:10.567
Bones, uh, tells me
that Daisy’s gonna be back
working in the lab.

01:10.655 --> 01:11.861
You gonna be okay with that?

01:11.989 --> 01:13.775
Of course, come on.
Why wouldn’t he be?

01:13.908 --> 01:15.694
Daisy is
an excellent intern.
Theyjust broke up.

01:15.826 --> 01:17.657
Well, that was
over a month ago.
Right.

01:17.745 --> 01:19.281
And yet he’s still
staying here with us.

01:19.372 --> 01:21.454
You believe he hasn’t yet
recovered emotionally...

01:21.540 --> 01:24.077
because he’s incapable
of finding an apartment?

01:24.168 --> 01:25.408
Don’t take a shrink
to know that one.

01:25.503 --> 01:27.869
— I’m standing right here,
you know.
— We see that.

01:27.964 --> 01:30.831
| just hope he doesn’t leave
before we find out
the secret to his coffee.

01:30.967 --> 01:32.423
It is truly
exceHent
It is good coffee.

01:32.551 --> 01:34.337
[ Booth ]
Yep, delicious.
Well, thank you.

01:34.428 --> 01:37.215
The housing market
in D.C.’s very tight, okay?

01:37.306 --> 01:40.548
— ljust don’t want to make
a choice that I’ll regret.
— Like Daisy?

01:40.643 --> 01:43.555
Okay, come on. It’s over.
I’m over it. I’m fine.

01:43.688 --> 01:44.677
Really?
Yeah.

01:44.772 --> 01:46.558
Have you had sex
with another woman yet?

01:46.649 --> 01:49.516
— Bones, we don’t have
to really discuss—
— It’s a valid question.

01:49.610 --> 01:52.818
I’m staying in Parker’s room.
Kind of hard to
bring home a woman...

01:52.905 --> 01:54.691
when you’re sleeping
on Wolverine sheets.

01:56.033 --> 01:58.319
[Rings]

01:58.411 --> 01:59.651
Booth.

01:59.745 --> 02:02.987
— So, no.
- Right.
Okay, on our way.

02:03.082 --> 02:05.698
Saddle up. We got a case.
Let’s just stay away from Daisy.

02:05.793 --> 02:07.124
You understand?

02:07.211 --> 02:08.872
Parker’s gonna want
to come home someday.

02:10.965 --> 02:13.627
Oh, I got to tell you.
Kind of hard to feel bad...

02:13.718 --> 02:16.630
for anybody who’d ride around
on a glorified scooter—
Whoa!

02:16.721 --> 02:19.884
There are signs of rodent
predation— squirrels and rats.

02:19.974 --> 02:24.308
First rodents, then maggots,
then the magnificent
rove beetles.

02:24.395 --> 02:27.228
It’s the circle of life.
Nothing is more beautiful.

02:27.315 --> 02:28.930
Okay, well,
I’m all choked up here.

02:29.025 --> 02:32.563
Not much tissue left,
but enough for a tox screen
and analysis.

02:32.653 --> 02:35.190
Brow ridge suggests
female Caucasian.

02:35.281 --> 02:38.944
The wear on the mandibular teeth
puts her in her early 30s.

02:39.035 --> 02:41.822
Kind of in the middle
of nowhere.

02:41.912 --> 02:43.413
I’m thinking sexual assault.

02:43.497 --> 02:45.237
Hard to tell until
we get her back to the lab,

02:45.333 --> 02:50.703
but I am seeing lacerations
and avulsions to the tissue
on the radius and the ulna.

02:50.796 --> 02:53.128
Maybe she was killed
someplace else and
brought here to be buried.

02:53.215 --> 02:56.582
It’s a shallow grave.
It’s a perfect place
for a body dump.

02:57.845 --> 02:59.585
Whoa, what’s that?

03:01.098 --> 03:03.555
Someone must have thought
it was an excellent place.

03:04.477 --> 03:06.433
There’s another body
in this grave.

03:14.862 --> 03:18.446
[ Brennan ] The chest cavity
on the first body we found
shows massive trauma...

03:18.532 --> 03:23.196
to the body of the sternum
and the bilateral fourth, fifth
and sixth sternal ribs.

03:23.287 --> 03:27.200
Including areas where
the periosteum is absent,
having abraded away.

03:27.291 --> 03:30.203
— Very good, Ms. Wick.
- Crushing fractures
at the point of impact...

03:30.294 --> 03:33.001
on both the right and
left radii and ulna.

03:33.089 --> 03:34.044
Defensive wounds.

03:34.131 --> 03:34.961
[ Together]
Yes.

03:36.759 --> 03:38.295
[ Chuckles ]
Great minds.

03:38.427 --> 03:41.214
I beg your pardon?
It’s like we’re operating
as one organism.

03:41.305 --> 03:44.593
Perhaps, if you view us
as a quantum physicist might.

03:44.683 --> 03:45.934
That would be fine.

03:46.060 --> 03:50.554
Are you all right,
Ms. Wick?
Of course. Why?

03:50.648 --> 03:53.060
| just thought
that you may be
a little anxious...

03:53.150 --> 03:55.687
that Dr. Sweets might be
dropping by the lab.

03:55.778 --> 03:59.316
Absolutely not.
I’m an emotional rock,
just like Dr. Brennan.

04:00.616 --> 04:02.447
Well, I hope so.

04:04.161 --> 04:05.947
Well, let’s get
the crime scene photos...

04:06.038 --> 04:08.450
and preliminary findings
to your... ex...

04:08.541 --> 04:11.624
and see if
he can put this burial
in a psychological context.

04:11.710 --> 04:13.211
Hmm.
Hmm.

04:51.375 --> 04:53.081
[ Booth ]
I don’t get it.

04:53.169 --> 04:54.909
No, it’s— It’s like Ophelia
in the brook.

04:55.045 --> 04:56.626
What, like Shakespeare?
Yeah,
Ham/er.

04:56.714 --> 04:58.124
Aw, don’t Ham/e! me,
okay?

04:58.215 --> 04:59.204
Thatstoo—
Dontdothat

