All right, all right.
What I mean to say is,

05:01.177 --> 05:03.384
the body was
arranged.
Right.

05:03.471 --> 05:05.382
Staged,
if you will.

05:05.473 --> 05:07.805
Now, the scarf
was placed under her chin,

05:07.892 --> 05:09.803
tied at the top of her head
to keep herjaw closed.

05:09.894 --> 05:12.852
Also, Hodgins confirmed that
the body was anointed...

05:12.938 --> 05:16.055
with sandalwood,
frankincense and cloves.

05:16.150 --> 05:17.731
You know,
you ever hear of green burials?

05:17.818 --> 05:20.901
Is that the, urn,
alternative death movement?

05:20.988 --> 05:23.445
No embalming, no coffin,
no cemetery?

05:23.532 --> 05:25.523
There it is. This company
called Green Passages.

05:25.618 --> 05:28.360
What they did is they leased
this burial site
from the national park...

05:28.454 --> 05:30.240
for a woman by the name
of Monica Craig.

05:30.331 --> 05:32.538
“Recycling your loved ones’
remains back into nature.”

05:32.625 --> 05:35.162
Da—da—da.
“More natural and
involved grieving process.”

05:35.294 --> 05:38.457
Yeah, this totally explains it.
But there should only be
one body there, not two.

05:38.589 --> 05:39.795
The funeral.
Yep.

05:39.882 --> 05:42.589
So what we have to do is
we got to get all the names...

05:42.676 --> 05:45.463
of everybody who knew
where Monica Craig was buried.

05:45.596 --> 05:47.587
Got it, Hamlet?
Oh, I’m doing that.

05:47.681 --> 05:48.636
Yep.

05:50.768 --> 05:52.679
[Angela ]
The victim’s name
is Monica Craig.

05:52.770 --> 05:54.886
Thirty—three years old.
Cancer victim.

05:54.980 --> 05:57.596
[ Brennan ]
“Monica Craig,
loving wife, beautiful spirit.

05:57.691 --> 06:00.398
Taken from us too soon
after a brave battle
with lung cancer.”

06:00.486 --> 06:03.899
But... how do you know
that Monica Craig was
the person...

06:03.989 --> 06:05.490
that we found in the grave?

06:05.574 --> 06:08.190
Well, the FBI.
traced the land to a company
that buries people...

06:08.285 --> 06:11.368
without embalming or coffins,
because it’s more natural.

06:11.455 --> 06:13.366
That’s true,
it is more natural.

06:13.457 --> 06:16.199
Yeah, well, fine by me,
but I wouldn’t tell
Hodgins that.

06:16.293 --> 06:18.329
He wants to be launched
into the sun...

06:18.420 --> 06:21.162
because he says that all life
came from the sun.

06:21.257 --> 06:23.498
That’s true—
All life does come from the sun.

06:23.592 --> 06:26.709
You know, you’re
very agreeable today,
just so you know.

06:26.804 --> 06:27.839
Thank you.

06:35.688 --> 06:36.677
Dr. Craig.

06:39.066 --> 06:40.522
l’m Dr. Lance Sweets.

06:40.609 --> 06:42.395
I’m a psychologist
with the FBI.

06:42.486 --> 06:44.067
This has to do with my wife?

06:44.154 --> 06:48.147
Yeah, and first, let me
pass on my condolences
for your recent loss.

06:49.326 --> 06:51.362
Thank you. But why am I here?

06:51.453 --> 06:52.954
Well, I’m sorry to have
to tell you that...

06:53.038 --> 06:55.154
your wife’s grave
has been recently
desecrated.

06:55.249 --> 06:58.366
What? What does
“desecrated” mean?

06:58.460 --> 07:00.166
Like, by Satanists or something?

07:00.254 --> 07:02.586
Someone used your wife’s
burial site to bury a body.

07:02.673 --> 07:06.632
You found another body?
In Monica’s grave?

07:06.719 --> 07:08.550
A murder victim.

07:10.764 --> 07:13.301
Where’s Monica now?
In the ensuing
invesﬂgaﬂon,

07:13.392 --> 07:15.804
her remains have been moved
to the Jeffersonian Institution.

07:15.894 --> 07:19.022
This is the opposite
of what Monica wanted.

07:19.106 --> 07:23.440
She just wanted to go
back into the universe
without any fuss.

07:23.527 --> 07:26.769
Well, we’re hoping
that you could provide
us a list...

07:26.864 --> 07:30.982
of everyone who knew
the location of
your wife’s grave.

07:31.076 --> 07:32.577
Yeah.
[ Clears Throat]

07:32.661 --> 07:36.950
It’s not a lot of people.
It’s just...
friends and family.

07:37.041 --> 07:39.373
None of them is a murderer.
None of them would—

07:39.460 --> 07:40.950
would dig—
who—who would do that?

07:41.045 --> 07:42.910
Who would do that
to another person?

07:43.005 --> 07:44.541
We’re gonna catch
whoever did this.

07:44.632 --> 07:49.217
[ Sighs ]
Is there anything else?

07:49.303 --> 07:51.089
Yeah.

07:53.140 --> 07:54.596
Do you know
this woman?

07:56.685 --> 07:58.221
Is this the—

07:58.312 --> 07:59.973
the body you found
in Monica’s grave?

08:00.064 --> 08:02.430
Yeah, that’s a reconstruction
of the face of the second woman.

08:02.566 --> 08:04.932
Do you recognize her?
Yes.

08:05.027 --> 08:07.268
That’s Rachel.
Rachel Knox.

08:07.363 --> 08:10.230
— How do you know her?
— She was Monica’s death doula.

08:10.324 --> 08:12.440
D— Um, excuse me?

08:12.534 --> 08:16.277
Um, Monica’s death consultant
at Green Passages.

08:16.372 --> 08:18.579
They were very close
before Monica died.

08:21.752 --> 08:25.085
You know, I thought that doulas
were for birth, not death.

08:25.172 --> 08:29.006
Doula is the feminine version of
the ancient Greek word “doulos,”

08:29.093 --> 08:31.209
which means servant
or caregiver.

08:31.303 --> 08:33.510
Right. Well, anyway,
Rachel Knox was the one...

08:33.597 --> 08:36.304
who helped Monica Craig
through her last days.

08:36.392 --> 08:38.303
You know, after death
she washed her body,

08:38.394 --> 08:40.760
dressed her, laid her
out for three days.

08:40.854 --> 08:44.346
Until the early 1800s,
it was unheard of
for most religions...

08:44.441 --> 08:48.684
to let a stranger
prepare and bury a loved one.

08:48.779 --> 08:51.191
When my time comes,
don’t do that.

08:51.281 --> 08:53.363
- When your time comes,
what should I do?
- My last will and testament,

08:53.450 --> 08:56.567
everything, it’s all written
out in the locked drawer
of my desk at work.

08:56.662 --> 08:59.153
My last will and testament
is 312 pages long.

08:59.248 --> 09:02.866
Whoa, geez. Mine’s written
on a sticky note.

09:02.960 --> 09:04.700
“Everything goes to Bones.”

09:04.795 --> 09:06.911
But don’t worry,
don’t worry.

09:07.005 --> 09:09.132
| used your real name
to make it legal.

09:09.216 --> 09:12.333
— What—What about Parker?
— Parker?
You’ll be fair to Parker.

09:12.428 --> 09:14.965
— On a sticky note?
- It’s like Gramps
always says, you know,

09:15.055 --> 09:18.388
if you tell God that things
are all wrapped up down here,

09:18.475 --> 09:20.056
he may feel free
to take you.

09:20.185 --> 09:21.595
[ Scoffs ]
There.

09:21.687 --> 09:23.803
All right, 312 pages?

09:23.897 --> 09:26.730
As you know, I have a lot
of money and investments.

09:26.817 --> 09:31.311
Also, I have
a complicated family,
and various income streams...

09:31.405 --> 09:33.771
that will continue after I die.

09:33.866 --> 09:35.822
But don’t worry,
you get some of it.

09:35.909 --> 09:37.490
Okay. Thanks.

09:37.578 --> 09:39.443
Most of it is set aside
for Christine.

09:39.580 --> 09:41.616
Right.
What about your funeral?

09:41.707 --> 09:45.950
Tell you what, you just give me
a coffin and a priest—
boom, I’ll be good to go.

09:46.044 --> 09:47.170
Okay.

09:47.254 --> 09:48.994
[ Exhales ]

09:50.090 --> 09:52.672
As you opened your heart
to us daily,

09:52.760 --> 09:55.467
so we shall carry you
in our hearts.

09:55.554 --> 09:56.919
Go for refuge, Aaron.

09:57.014 --> 10:00.097
[All]
Buddha, dharma, sangha.

10:00.184 --> 10:03.676
Your soul is part
of the air and light, Aaron,

10:03.771 --> 10:06.888
the unknowable greatness
that is the universe.

10:06.982 --> 10:08.438
Go for refuge.

10:08.525 --> 10:11.232
[All]
Buddha, dharma, sangha.

10:11.320 --> 10:14.357
As you opened your heart
to us daily, so we—

10:14.448 --> 10:18.862
— What?
- This is modeled after
a... traditional prayer.

10:18.952 --> 10:20.817
Part of the Buddhist
funeral rites.

10:20.913 --> 10:22.904
Well, that’s pretty—
Hey, look at that—

10:23.040 --> 10:24.200
It’s our victim. Oh!
Booth!

10:29.296 --> 10:31.457
Sorry.
Uh, no disrespect.

10:31.548 --> 10:33.288
— What are you doing?
- I made a mistake.

10:33.383 --> 10:36.045
Just go back to
your chanting or your—

10:36.136 --> 10:38.127
l have approximately
two weeks to live.

10:38.222 --> 10:40.213
My friends and l are
practicing my internment rite.

10:40.307 --> 10:41.922
Aaron, it’s okay.

10:42.017 --> 10:43.882
Practicing... to be dead?

10:43.977 --> 10:47.265
This is, um—
You know, death is a difficult
topic in our culture,

10:47.356 --> 10:51.395
and practice and preparation
demystifies the process, so—

10:51.485 --> 10:53.476
You must be the director
of Green Passages.

10:53.570 --> 10:56.186
- Akshay Mirza, yes.
- Is he, like, the death doula?

10:59.034 --> 11:02.117
Okay.
Well, we’re also here
about the end of a life.

11:02.204 --> 11:06.117
Your associate,
Rachel Knox, is dead.

11:14.258 --> 11:16.499
I can’t believe
that Rachel is gone.

11:16.593 --> 11:18.379
Uh, she was your
business partner?

11:18.470 --> 11:20.847
Uh,yeah,yeah.
We’d been doing this
for about two years.

11:20.931 --> 11:23.092
She was found dead yesterday
in one of your grave sites.

11:23.183 --> 11:25.390
One of our sites?
Are you sure?

11:25.477 --> 11:26.762
Yes.
Monica Craig’s.

11:27.938 --> 11:29.553
Oh, God.

11:29.648 --> 11:32.811
Uh, wait.
Are you sure it was Rachel?
You’re positive?

11:32.901 --> 11:37.361
The mandible
and dental evidence
confirm her identity.

11:37.447 --> 11:40.610
Okay. Okay.

11:41.910 --> 11:45.118
I don’t know what
I’m going to do without—

11:45.205 --> 11:47.241
I got to sit.

11:48.417 --> 11:50.328
You okay?
Thoughtyou,uh,

11:50.460 --> 11:54.203
dealt with death
all the time.
Not for someone I know.

11:54.298 --> 11:56.505
This is a first for me.

11:56.592 --> 11:59.550
And take deep breaths
through your nose...

11:59.636 --> 12:01.797
to avoid
hyperventilation.

12:01.889 --> 12:06.883
You know, we are told that
existence is impermanent
and conditional,

12:06.977 --> 12:09.889
and that the pain
that we feel is just
a natural product of that.

12:09.980 --> 12:12.392
Right. Okay.
She was, uh, murdered,
uh, three weeks ago.

12:12.524 --> 12:14.355
Why didn’t you
report her missing?
Oh, no, no.

12:14.443 --> 12:17.901
No, Rachel disappeared
all the time.
It’s who she was.

12:17.988 --> 12:20.900
That must have
made you angry, huh?
Her being away all the time.

12:20.991 --> 12:22.481
It must have been bad
for business.

12:22.576 --> 12:25.693
No, no. It allowed Rachel
to connect more fully
to her clients.

12:25.787 --> 12:28.574
And business was growing.
It was up 60%
from last year to this.

12:28.665 --> 12:31.532
Her death appears to
have been extremely violent.

12:31.627 --> 12:33.458
Can you think of anyone
who’d want to hurt her?

12:33.545 --> 12:37.754
Hurt her? No. God, no.
No, no. Rachel was loved.

12:37.841 --> 12:42.130
She wouldn’t take on a client
unless she could give herself
over completely to them.

12:42.220 --> 12:44.256
Okay, well,
if you can think of anyone
who wanted to hurt her—

12:44.348 --> 12:47.465
ex—boyfriend, a client—
you can just
give me a call.

12:47.559 --> 12:49.936
- There’s my card.
Special Agent Seeley Booth.
— Sure.

12:50.020 --> 12:51.055
Let’s go, Bones.

12:53.523 --> 12:55.855
We have to go now,
Mr. Mirza.

12:57.569 --> 13:00.026
Could I have my hand back?

13:01.448 --> 13:03.655
I don’t know
how I’m going to get
through this without Ra—

13:13.251 --> 13:15.207
[ Daisy]
Dr. Hodgins, I’d like you
to take a look at this.

13:16.546 --> 13:17.831
See the comminuted
fracture...

13:17.923 --> 13:19.788
at the distal end
of the sternal body,

13:19.883 --> 13:21.748
just superior to
the xiphisternal joint?

13:21.843 --> 13:23.299
She was really crushed.

13:23.387 --> 13:25.298
A blow this hard is likely
the cause of death.

13:25.389 --> 13:28.176
It would push the sternum
back into the heart.

13:28.266 --> 13:31.303
And if, in that second,
the ventricle was filled
to maximum capacity,

13:31.395 --> 13:32.885
the bone
would pop the heart.

13:32.980 --> 13:35.096
The bone was like a pin
in a balloon.

13:35.190 --> 13:36.726
More like a stick of
dynamite in a balloon.

13:36.817 --> 13:38.933
Given the amount ofjagged
edges on the fracturing,

13:39.069 --> 13:40.559
I thought—
There might be some
particulates in there.

13:40.654 --> 13:42.019
Yeah, okay.
I’ll take a look.

13:42.114 --> 13:43.479
I’m hoping that this
is more productive...

13:43.573 --> 13:44.983
than pulverizing
the rove beetles,

13:45.075 --> 13:47.441
because the mass spec
showed nothing.

13:47.536 --> 13:50.903
You seem good,
like you’re totally okay
after breaking up with Sweets.

13:50.998 --> 13:53.831
I am. Now that
I’m focusing solely
on my career in science,

13:53.917 --> 13:55.418
lbeHeve
my life is together.

13:55.502 --> 13:58.164
Well, thank God, because
there is nothing more painful...

13:58.255 --> 14:00.667
than watching an ex—couple
do the awkward dance.

14:00.757 --> 14:03.669
I assure you,
I’ll handle seeing Lance
in a professional way.

14:03.760 --> 14:05.591
Or you’ll want to stab him.

14:05.679 --> 14:08.170
I mean, he did dump you
on the night you were
going to move in together.

14:08.265 --> 14:09.550
I’m not a child,
Dr. Hodgins.

14:09.683 --> 14:11.139
No, ljust thought—
I’m sure you did.

14:11.226 --> 14:14.309
But idle gossip is not
going to help us
solve this murder.

14:14.396 --> 14:17.980
Perhaps a bone scraping
would provide a more detailed
analysis than a swab.

14:18.066 --> 14:19.931
You could analyze
your findings using...

14:20.027 --> 14:23.064
not only under stereo,
compound and polarizing
microscopes,

14:23.155 --> 14:25.020
but also using
an energy dispersive X-ray.

14:25.115 --> 14:27.071
That’s what Dr. Brennan
would do as well.

14:27.159 --> 14:30.868
Wow.
You really have pulled
yourself together.

14:30.954 --> 14:33.411
You’re welcome,
Dr. Hodgins.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.792
Well, Sweets said
that Dr. Craig...

14:39.880 --> 14:42.246
just filed a lawsuit
against Green Passages...

14:42.340 --> 14:44.126
for desecration
of his wife’s grave,

14:44.217 --> 14:46.173
which I cannot say
that I blame him for.

14:46.261 --> 14:47.876
Booth is checking
with their other clients...

14:47.971 --> 14:50.178
to see if anyone else
had a problem with them.

14:50.265 --> 14:53.052
Hmm. None of the other
burial sites were disturbed.

14:53.143 --> 14:58.354
He thinks that maybe
Rachel wasn’t quite
as saintly as Akshay said.

14:58.440 --> 15:00.977
Looks like this
death business
can be lethal, huh?

15:01.068 --> 15:03.810
[Laughs]
That is amusing.

15:03.904 --> 15:06.441
Because we’re
investigating a murder.

15:06.573 --> 15:11.237
Right.
The juxtaposition
of funerals and a killing—

15:11.369 --> 15:14.076
[Laughs]
Most people would
just laugh, sweetie.

15:14.164 --> 15:15.745
I’m sor/y

15:15.832 --> 15:17.868
Checked out all lawsuits
that were filed
against Green Passages.

15:18.001 --> 15:19.502
There’s Dr. Craig’s—
Understandable.

15:19.586 --> 15:22.043
and three other suits
that were filed
by this guy, Mick Warren.

15:22.130 --> 15:24.337
Three?
Did he have a burial
site desecrated too?

15:24.424 --> 15:28.713
No. He owned two cemeteries.
And all the suits
named Rachel Knox individually.

15:28.845 --> 15:30.710
Fraud, breach of promise.
Angry stuff.

15:30.847 --> 15:32.712
Yeah, he was trying
to put her out of business.
Hmm.

15:32.849 --> 15:35.761
But you’re thinking,
if that didn’t work—
Bingo.

15:35.852 --> 15:37.717
Thanks for waiting there,
Mr. Warren.

15:37.813 --> 15:40.225
This here is Dr. Sweets.
He’s going to be joining us.

15:40.357 --> 15:43.349
Dr. Sweets.
Please,
have a seat.

15:43.485 --> 15:47.103
I sure am sorry
to hear about Rachel.
Yeah.

15:47.197 --> 15:49.483
She was a sweet thing.

15:49.574 --> 15:53.613
Little loony with all
the New Age stuff,
but sweet.

15:53.745 --> 15:56.782
You and Rachel
were business competitors?
Nothing wrong with that.

15:56.873 --> 15:58.989
Competition is what makes
this country great.

15:59.084 --> 16:01.700
According to this suit
you filed,

16:01.837 --> 16:05.671
Rachel reneged on a promise
to go into business together?
Yes, she did.

16:05.757 --> 16:08.043
She had the land that was
licensed for green burials,

16:08.135 --> 16:10.046
and l have a strong brand.

16:10.137 --> 16:12.002
lthought
we’d do well together.

16:12.139 --> 16:15.131
Even though she was a loony?
The boomers are dying,
you know?

16:15.225 --> 16:17.637
There’s a fortune to be made
on all these bozos...

16:17.727 --> 16:19.854
driving around
in their electric cars,

16:19.938 --> 16:22.179
wanting to know the names
of the chickens they’re eating.

16:22.274 --> 16:23.889
You do understand
her backing out...

16:23.984 --> 16:25.599
gives you a strong motive
to kill her.

16:25.694 --> 16:27.776
Yeah, I wanted
to wipe her out.

16:27.863 --> 16:31.321
In court.
We had a deal.

16:31.408 --> 16:33.114
She takes up
with this Mirza,

16:33.201 --> 16:34.782
and she reneges
on the whole thing.

16:34.911 --> 16:36.993
When you say “takes up with”?
[ Scoffs ]

16:37.080 --> 16:40.618
What do you think?
They started
sleeping together.

16:40.709 --> 16:42.040
I guess he gave her
what she wanted,

16:42.127 --> 16:43.992
and she gave him
what I wanted.

16:44.087 --> 16:47.625
Oh, wait a minute.
[ Chuckles ]

16:47.716 --> 16:50.048
You guys didn’t know
