last message look like?

31:24.425 --> 31:26.507
l’ve planned
for a celestial funeral.

31:26.594 --> 31:28.630
Also known as
a Tibetan sky funeral.

31:28.721 --> 31:31.838
The deceased is carried
to a mountain plateau...

31:31.932 --> 31:35.424
where a lama burial master
breaks the body.

31:36.270 --> 31:38.727
Breaks the body?
Dismembers.

31:38.814 --> 31:44.059
Then pulverizes with a hammer,
which allows for optimum
scavenging by vultures.

31:45.321 --> 31:47.061
You’re messing with me.
Come on.

31:47.156 --> 31:49.192
My instructions
are very explicit.

31:49.283 --> 31:52.525
To give yourself to the air.
lt’s—lt’s a beautiful ceremony.

31:52.620 --> 31:54.110
Vultures and hammers?

31:54.205 --> 31:57.117
That’s your—your last message
to the world? To me?

31:57.208 --> 31:58.698
To Christine?

31:58.793 --> 32:01.284
Vultures and hammers.

32:02.213 --> 32:04.204
I’m gonna go get the car.

32:06.258 --> 32:07.464
[ Exhales ]

32:07.551 --> 32:10.042
[ Door Opens, Closes]

32:15.935 --> 32:17.766
My wife died
of cancer.

32:17.853 --> 32:20.686
And I’m trying to figure out
if you really believe that.

32:23.776 --> 32:26.893
What’s that?
It’s a banned substance
called methylone.

32:26.987 --> 32:29.114
You know it?

32:29.240 --> 32:31.526
No.
Sir, you’re gonna have
to stop lying to me.

32:31.617 --> 32:34.700
You used methylone to treat
depression in your practice
before it was banned.

32:34.787 --> 32:36.243
No, no, no. No. No.

32:36.330 --> 32:37.740
Your wife died
of a methylone overdose.

32:37.832 --> 32:40.164
I did not murder my wife.

32:43.003 --> 32:45.790
Well, what some people
call murder,

32:45.881 --> 32:47.792
others might call mercy.

32:55.015 --> 32:56.551
Monica begged me.

32:58.018 --> 33:01.055
Okay?
She was in terrible pain.

33:02.064 --> 33:03.725
My wife— she loved life,

33:03.816 --> 33:05.681
but this was not life.

33:06.902 --> 33:08.688
She kept telling me
if! loved her—

33:08.821 --> 33:11.904
You helped her.
No, I did not help her.

33:13.659 --> 33:15.570
But I did not stop her.

33:23.127 --> 33:25.789
What happens to me now?
What do you mean?

33:25.880 --> 33:28.667
Well, ljust confessed
to allowing my wife
to kill herself.

33:28.757 --> 33:32.545
[ Sighs ]
Well, we’re looking
for a murderer.

33:32.636 --> 33:34.422
What happens
now is...

33:34.513 --> 33:36.754
you go home.

33:42.938 --> 33:46.021
...Seeley Joseph Booth,
of Washington DC,

33:46.108 --> 33:49.191
revoke my former
will and codicils...

33:49.278 --> 33:51.394
written on a sticky note?

33:51.488 --> 33:54.150
[Sighs]
This is—

33:54.241 --> 33:55.856
This thing sucks.

33:55.951 --> 33:57.907
So, I wrote up my
findings on Wes Craig.

33:57.995 --> 33:59.951
His grief is very real.

34:00.039 --> 34:02.075
The guilt he feels is
attached to the fact...

34:02.166 --> 34:05.078
that he provided Monica Craig
with the drugs she used
to kill herself.

34:05.211 --> 34:07.167
And he has guilt?
Oh, yeah.

34:07.254 --> 34:10.667
One might even say he displays
more signifiers of guilt
than he does of grief,

34:10.758 --> 34:12.339
though the two
are inextricably linked.

34:12.426 --> 34:15.668
Sometimes when a loved one dies,
we feel survivor’s guilt.

34:15.763 --> 34:18.049
You probably felt it
yourself in the military.

34:18.140 --> 34:21.007
So you’re saying
all the phone calls that
Craig made to Rachel Knox...

34:21.143 --> 34:22.644
indicate his state of mind?
Yes.

34:22.728 --> 34:25.140
The number of calls
he made per day increased...

34:25.231 --> 34:27.517
as the day
of his wife’s suicide
drew nearer.

34:27.608 --> 34:29.564
[Sighs]

34:29.693 --> 34:31.604
What?
He starts out calling,

34:31.695 --> 34:33.196
say, what, once a week
for a while.

34:33.280 --> 34:34.895
Then... several times a day.

34:35.032 --> 34:36.522
Right.
Right.

34:36.617 --> 34:38.153
Take a look.

34:39.203 --> 34:40.943
I don’t know
what I’m looking for.

34:41.038 --> 34:42.699
The timeline.
There’s a pattern.

34:44.750 --> 34:45.956
Wow.

34:46.085 --> 34:48.872
Yeah.
The period of time he made
all these phone calls.

34:48.963 --> 34:50.499
Just over three months
and then they stop.

34:50.589 --> 34:52.875
Two days before
his wife’s death.

34:52.967 --> 34:54.707
Three months.

34:54.802 --> 34:57.544
That’s the period
of time Rachel Knox would
sleep with any one man.

34:58.639 --> 35:00.755
You want me to talk
to him again?
No.

35:00.849 --> 35:02.350
l have this one.

35:14.196 --> 35:16.357
This room’s even scarier
than the last one.

35:19.535 --> 35:21.821
And you’re scarier
than the psychologist.

35:21.912 --> 35:23.573
You know what?
According to our records,

35:23.664 --> 35:26.872
you made 405 phone calls
to Rachel Knox in three months.

35:26.959 --> 35:29.871
No. These—These calls,
they were all about Monica.

35:31.213 --> 35:32.828
You know
what I’m thinking?

35:32.923 --> 35:34.879
I’m thinking,
why would a man use...

35:34.967 --> 35:37.709
a wife’s tombstone
to kill someone?

35:37.803 --> 35:40.465
Why? You had an affair
with Rachel Knox.

35:40.556 --> 35:41.796
I did not admit to that.

35:41.890 --> 35:44.506
Rachel Knox advised you
to euthanize your wife.

35:44.601 --> 35:46.216
My wife killed herself.

35:46.312 --> 35:47.643
Our shrink says that she didn’t.

35:47.730 --> 35:50.972
I mean, if she did,
then”.

35:51.066 --> 35:54.604
you wouldn’t be
feeling guilty.

35:54.737 --> 35:57.353
What else did he say?
He says that only
a guilty husband...

35:57.448 --> 36:00.940
would put the special
grave marker back
exactly where it was.

36:03.245 --> 36:04.701
After I killed Rachel with it?

36:04.788 --> 36:06.574
Exactly.

36:07.916 --> 36:09.076
That’s a lot of guilt.

36:09.168 --> 36:11.409
He says you loved your wife,
but you cheated on her.

36:12.588 --> 36:15.125
[ Sighs ]
With Rachel Knox.

36:15.215 --> 36:16.796
Three months.

36:17.634 --> 36:19.420
Three months.

36:21.013 --> 36:23.129
l was supposed to think
that was a real thing?

36:23.223 --> 36:28.183
You know, three months
fell exactly two days
before Monica died.

36:28.270 --> 36:31.933
Then, l’m—l’m placing
the stone, and...

36:32.024 --> 36:34.857
she shows up to plant the tree.

36:36.487 --> 36:38.023
And she tells me—

36:38.113 --> 36:39.569
She hits me
with that yoga babble,

36:39.656 --> 36:42.193
like I wasn’t even
a real person anymore.

36:42.284 --> 36:44.775
“Our time is over.”

36:46.455 --> 36:48.912
I mean, I couldn’t—
I couldn’t lose somebody else.

36:49.708 --> 36:51.790
Not after Monica.

36:53.504 --> 36:56.792
[ Sobbing ]

