Okay.

37:52.354 --> 37:54.310
Actually,

37:56.233 --> 37:58.064
I’m feeling quite sad.

37:58.152 --> 37:59.642
About Sweets?

38:02.030 --> 38:03.531
I know I shouldn’t.

38:06.535 --> 38:08.150
I’m so stable, and...

38:09.288 --> 38:12.030
we agreed that we shouldn’t
get back together.

38:13.083 --> 38:15.290
But what if we’re wrong?
You’re grieving.

38:15.377 --> 38:20.371
You two had something
alive and vibrant, and...
now it’s gone.

38:20.466 --> 38:22.457
But what if we can
bring it back to life?

38:22.551 --> 38:25.588
You’re a scientist, Ms. Wick.
A very good scientist.

38:25.721 --> 38:27.712
Thank you.
As a scientist,

38:27.806 --> 38:31.424
have you ever seen anything
come back to life
and be as good as it ever was?

38:35.856 --> 38:36.811
No.

38:36.899 --> 38:40.266
So feel sad. Cry.

38:40.360 --> 38:43.397
You lost something wonderful,
but keep moving forward.

38:45.240 --> 38:47.026
It’ll get better.

38:47.117 --> 38:49.278
I promise.

38:54.166 --> 38:56.282
And, uh—

38:56.376 --> 38:58.583
Stop copying Dr. Brennan.
It’s a little creepy.

39:08.472 --> 39:10.588
On here.

39:10.682 --> 39:12.673
Okay.

39:14.311 --> 39:18.930
[ Sighs ]
Hey there, Christine.

39:19.816 --> 39:22.068
It’s me, your father.

39:25.781 --> 39:29.399
If you’re watching this
right now, I’m dead.

39:32.454 --> 39:33.955
Um,

39:34.039 --> 39:36.451
if I was a good
father to you,

39:37.417 --> 39:41.456
you’re... sad right now.

39:43.423 --> 39:46.631
If we had some sort of,
like, falling out,

39:47.970 --> 39:50.336
let’s just forget about it
and move on.

39:50.430 --> 39:52.261
It’s just—
It’s not worth it.

39:53.892 --> 39:56.975
You know, personally,
I’m doing everything I can
to get into heaven...

39:57.062 --> 39:58.268
right now, um—

39:58.355 --> 40:02.394
But your mother believes—
Well, she thinks that it’s a—

40:02.484 --> 40:05.851
I tell you what,
why don’t you ask her?

40:05.946 --> 40:08.983
lt’s... complicated.

40:09.074 --> 40:14.535
These are the last... words...

40:14.621 --> 40:19.786
that I’m going to—to speak
in this world, so here goes.

40:19.876 --> 40:21.412
Okay.

40:21.503 --> 40:25.542
I like God.
I really like God, and l—
and I think that he likes me.

40:27.092 --> 40:30.710
You know, I, um—
I love Canadian beer.
And hockey.

40:30.804 --> 40:32.635
They kind of go hand in hand.
[ Chuckles ]

40:32.723 --> 40:37.467
I really love loud music
and really sad music.

40:37.561 --> 40:39.893
I love this country.

40:41.023 --> 40:44.186
And I’m proud to have served
in the military.

40:46.194 --> 40:48.856
I’m the luckiest man...

40:48.947 --> 40:52.781
in the world because I got to
spend time with your mother...

40:55.329 --> 40:57.194
and with you.

41:04.755 --> 41:06.461
[Sighs]

41:06.548 --> 41:10.291
And that’s true, you know?
It’s true whether I...

41:10.385 --> 41:13.752
I die today or 50 years
from now. It’s true.

41:13.847 --> 41:15.883
Okay?

41:17.309 --> 41:23.100
I love you.
And I want you to—
to love life.

41:24.232 --> 41:26.359
Dive into life. Be—

41:26.443 --> 41:30.607
Be courageous.
Question things.

41:30.697 --> 41:32.938
And— And be happy.

41:33.033 --> 41:34.944
Don’t forget to laugh.

41:35.035 --> 41:38.448
Oh, one last favor.
Um—

41:38.538 --> 41:41.245
Help your mom to be happy.

41:41.333 --> 41:45.076
Because if she’s alone,
she’s gonna forget.

41:51.843 --> 41:53.834
That’s it. That’s—

41:53.929 --> 41:57.012
From me to you.

41:57.683 --> 41:59.514
[ Kisses ]

41:59.601 --> 42:01.762
Whoa!
Okay. All right.

42:01.895 --> 42:04.762
I’m still alive, Bones.
And you know what?
You shouldn’t be eavesdropping.

42:04.856 --> 42:06.847
And you messed the end up here.
Now I have to change it.

42:06.942 --> 42:08.182
l’m sorry.
Well—

42:08.318 --> 42:11.151
l-l listened to
you too, Booth.
Huh?

42:11.238 --> 42:12.227
Look.

42:13.323 --> 42:15.188
[ Booth ]
Hey.
Ta—da!

42:15.325 --> 42:16.861
You changed your will.
Yes.

42:16.952 --> 42:19.864
I find that despite
my best efforts,

42:19.955 --> 42:21.991
you exert undue influence
on my behavior.

42:22.124 --> 42:24.615
Wait, I got to read
this whole thing?
No, no.

42:24.751 --> 42:28.118
It’s 306 pages.
306 pages?

42:28.255 --> 42:30.211
It’s less than 312.
Oh, wow.

42:30.298 --> 42:32.380
But look. Here.

42:32.509 --> 42:34.545
I changed the nature
of my funeral.
Mm—hmm.

42:34.636 --> 42:36.467
Take a look.

42:38.432 --> 42:39.387
A volcano?

42:39.474 --> 42:41.681
Yes. I remember
you telling me...

42:41.768 --> 42:44.259
that you’d very much like
to visit an active volcano.

42:44.396 --> 42:47.809
Okay, you want us to sprinkle
your ashes over a volcano?
Yes.

42:47.899 --> 42:50.641
That way,
at least if I’m dead,

42:50.736 --> 42:53.728
you can have
a nice trip together
and foolishly risk your lives.

42:53.864 --> 42:56.606
Which will bring us
closer together. Yeah?
Yes.

42:56.742 --> 42:58.403
Hey—
You’re welcome.

42:58.493 --> 43:00.905
But wait a second,
how am I gonna get
to the top of the volcano?

43:01.037 --> 43:03.449
It’s not my problem.
